  abstract  = {This seminal paper details the physical and energetic causes of the urban heat island phenomenon, emphasizing how urban surface materials, such as concrete and asphalt prevalent in built-up areas, possess higher thermal admittance and conductivity compared to natural surfaces. This leads to increased absorption and storage of solar radiation, contributing significantly to elevated land surface temperatures and the UHI effect.}
